# Component Structure

## Required Directory Structure
Every component and screen must follow this structure:
```
ComponentName/
├── index.tsx        # Main component file (JSX & minimal logic)
├── scripts.ts       # Business logic and utilities
├── styles.ts        # Styled components or styles
└── types.ts         # TypeScript interfaces and types
```

## File Responsibilities

### index.tsx
- React component definition only
- JSX structure
- Basic hooks (useState, useEffect)
- Props handling
- Import statements
- NO business logic

### scripts.ts
- All business logic
- Helper functions (use descriptive verbs)
- Constants in UPPERCASE_SNAKE_CASE
- Calculations & transformations
- Animation logic
- Event handlers
- Complex hooks

### styles.ts
- styled-components or StyleSheet.create()
- All styling logic
- Theme variables
- NO inline styles in components

### types.ts
- All interfaces and types
- Clear, descriptive names
- Export all definitions

## Migration Process
1. Always start with types
2. Move logic to scripts.ts
3. Keep components clean and presentational
4. No business logic in components